14 presumed Drogendealer arrests
On Wednesday in the context of smashing a production and sales sale by cannabis around the ten house searches in the administrative region Estrie were made.
Fourteen persons were arrested thereby and were opposite placed different accusations.
The house searches took place in Sherbrooke, Orford and Stoke, to which places those are to have predominantly served the drug production.
" Approximately 750 Cannabispflanzen, four Kilos hashish, cash and equipment, which served production, are konfisziert worden" , Louis Philippe Ruel, speaker of the state police of Quebec indicated.
Altogether eleven men and three women were arrested, from whom two of the men, who are considered as main wire-pullers of the drug ring, originate from Sherbrooke.
The arrested persons are to have appeared already hours after their arrest before the law courts in Sherbrooke.
They could among other things the accusation of the production of cannabis, whose possession for sales purposes, the plot as well as the service of crimes are accused.
These house searches had taken place in consequence of a lengthy investigating activity, which went over one year long.
" The information received from public institutions made it for us possible, durchzuführen" these arrests; , M. Ruel specified.
Around the 70 policemen of the regional investigation unit Estrien of the state police of the Quebec, the police service Sherbrooke as well as the police authority Memphrémagog in this police operation had participated.
